{"name": "Efficient Shorthand", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-writing-brown-grey.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have developed a simple yet efficient system for categorizing, sorting, and copying knowledge. The cost of copying spells into a spellbook is halved for you.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Wizard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "RO9FKOQD6XCS0KNA", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Information Overload", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/wounds/anatomy-organ-brain-pink-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When you cast a spell that has one of the following damage types in the description: acid, cold, fire, force, lightning, radiant, poison, or necrotic, you can replace the damage type with psychic and the spell&rsquo;s appearance changes to accommodate.</p><p>Whenever you modify a spell in this way, any Dexterity and Constitution (Save) Checks are replaced with Intelligence (Save) Checks.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Have the Wizard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "9NG1O17IMMJWQ96D", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Mnemonic Incantation", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/diplomacy-offering-ritual.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Ritual casting a spell now only takes 1 additional minute instead of 10 additional minutes.</p><p>In addition, once per long rest, you can spend mana to cast an unprepared spell from your spellbook with the Ritual tag as if it was prepared.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Have the Wizard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "1MU42OBYA856G0UH", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Redundant Records", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/fire/flame-burning-campfire-rocks.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>Unlock: </em>When you reach 6th level overall you may take the ability below.</p><p>As a minor action, you can tear the pages containing a single non-Legendary spell from one of your spellbooks and spend half of the spell's mana cost (rounded down) to imbue them with the power of a spell scroll for the corresponding spell. The chosen spell is removed from your spellbook. The pages crumble to ash after the spell is cast.</p><p>Once you use this ability you can't use it again until you finish a long rest.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Have the Wizard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "8T2WMB6IJSJBDOAY", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Supplementary Materials", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/books/book-stack.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have created a system of backups and organization, called Supplemental Spellbooks, that helps reduce the mental load of studying spells.&nbsp;</p><p>Each time you prepare your list of spells for the day, you can select one of your Supplemental Spellbooks to memorize. The spells in the chosen Supplemental Spellbook are prepared for that day and do not count against the total number of spells you can prepare.</p><p>A Supplemental Spellbook can be any book that you copy spells into as long as the number of spells contained within is no greater than your proficiency bonus and at least one of the following holds true:</p><ul><li>Every spell in the book belongs to the same school of magic.</li><li>Every spell in the book is of the same level.</li><li>The name of every spell in the book begins with the same letter.</li></ul><p>Whenever you select this ability, as a result of your experimentation and rough drafts you start with one ready to use Supplemental Spellbook which contains a copy of any two spells already in your spellbook (your chosen combination of spells must satisfy the requirements to be Supplemental Spellbook).</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Have the Wizard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "EWZ01SQKAEZX64W7", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Trove of Knowledge", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/containers/chest/chest-simple-purple.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As an archivist you value knowledge itself more highly than others, and there are few things you wouldn't part with to obtain it. To this end, you know how to perform a ritual over a short rest that allows you to transmute up to 300 gp worth of valuable stones or metals, accompanied by bottles of fresh water, into spell ink and scribing materials with an equivalent value.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Wizard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "SN7OJX8K8CW54ZOO", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Athletic", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You can accomplish impressive feats of physical endurance. You gain proficiency in Strength (Athletics).</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "2nd level overall and have at least one level in a Martial class", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "VXLO74M9FQ5TRHU8", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Going All-Out", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/unholy/strike-body-life-soul-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>After taking a desperate action, you can choose to act normally on your next turn, but cannot take desperate actions until then. Once you use this ability, you can't use it again until you finish a short rest.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "2nd level overall and have at least one level in a Martial class", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "KHXTYYWW0CRFP2RN", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Sprinter", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/movement/figure-running-gray.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your base walking speed increases by 10 feet, and attacks of opportunity against you have disadvantage.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "2nd level overall and have at least one level in a Martial class", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "GOP7M90B2MXBCL8K", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Stalwart Physique", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/wounds/injury-body-pain-gray.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You can use Constitution in place of Dexterity when determining your AC. While you aren't wearing any armor, your AC is 12 + Your Dexterity or Constitution Modifier.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "2nd level overall and have at least one level in a Martial class", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "17YBBWEXS5QW6W94", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Tireless", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/time/day-night-sunset-sunrise.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>Unlock: </em>When you reach 6th level overall you may take the ability below.</p><p>When you have @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.ERBR3AG01H4N1L91]{Exhaustion}, you suffer its effects as if you had half as many levels of @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.ERBR3AG01H4N1L91]{Exhaustion} (rounded down). Whenever you remove @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.ERBR3AG01H4N1L91]{Exhaustion} as part of a long rest, you can remove an additional level of @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.ERBR3AG01H4N1L91]{Exhaustion}.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "2nd level overall and have at least one level in a Martial class", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "MCOVKJ7UZMJQGXIQ", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Center Stage", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/light/beam-strike-village-yellow.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As an action, you can spend 2 @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE]{&#x2728; Flair} points to conjure a 15ft radius, 60ft tall cylinder of bright light centered on a point you can see that lasts for 1 minute. While a creature is inside the light, it is @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.ZOBZ8V2YME5YOYZR]{&#x1F981; Lionized} if it is an ally to you or @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.WHN3T2G6R8HUKOQX]{&#x1F9FF; Villainized} if it is hostile to you. Until the ability ends, you can use either your action or 1 @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE]{&#x2728; Flair} point and a minor action to move the cylinder of light to another point you can see within 60 ft of you.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "adept"}, "requirements": "6th level overall and 3rd level Bard", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "0U3IYHVQDRO4RJXM", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Commit to the Bit", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/intimidation-impressing.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You know your talents are best employed with the backing of a capable troupe, and can spot opportunities to make each member shine.</p><p>Any time you take the <strong>Assist</strong> action, you can also cause the creature to become @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.ZOBZ8V2YME5YOYZR]{&amp;#x1F981; Lionized}&nbsp;until the end of your next turn.</p><p>Additionally, as part of an <strong>Assist</strong> action, you can choose to support the creature throughout its next turn. If you commit in this way, you must move alongside the creature in such a way that you remain adjacent until the end of its next turn. You can accompany the creature regardless of your speed, so long as you could have otherwise traversed the path on your own.&nbsp;</p><p>While accompanying the creature, this creature has advantage on the first attack roll it makes before the end of its turn, and before the attack roll is made you can @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.WHN3T2G6R8HUKOQX]{&amp;#x1F9FF; Villainize} the target of the attack until the end of your next turn.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Bard", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "U9Y7QXOXOYNA04W7", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Dynamic Duo", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You are at your most effective when you&rsquo;ve got someone to back up your act, and you can provide ample support in return. You can augment your <strong>Assist</strong> action in the following ways:</p><ul><li>When you take the <strong>Assist</strong> action, you can make a single weapon attack as a minor action. If you <strong>Commit to the Bit</strong>, you can choose to delay this attack until you are within range of a target on the assisted creature&rsquo;s turn.</li><li>When you take the <strong>Assist</strong> action, you can use your minor action to cast a cantrip with a normal casting time of one action. If you <strong>Commit to the Bit</strong>, you can instead use your minor action to cast a 1st level spell with a normal casting time of one action. A 1st level spell cast in this way can only affect you, the assisted creature, and objects carried by either of you.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "adept"}, "requirements": "6th level overall and 3rd level Bard", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "FHJRNZE4BO3NRACH", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Flair", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/light/hand-sparks-smoke-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As a Bard, you can draw upon the attention and creative imagination of others to sculpt and add style to the progression of events, be they fictional or real. This potential is represented by your @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE]{&#x2728; Flair} points, which you can use to fuel various Bard abilities. Generally, this will involve applying the @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.ZOBZ8V2YME5YOYZR]{&#x1F981; Lionized} or @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.WHN3T2G6R8HUKOQX]{&#x1F9FF; Villainized} conditions to a creature.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Your maximum @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE]{&#x2728; Flair} points is 2. The maximum increases for every odd-numbered Bard level gained, starting at Bard level 3.  For example, at Bard level 8, you can hold a maximum of 5 @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE]{&#x2728; Flair} points. If you would gain a @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE]{&#x2728; Flair} point while already at your maximum you become @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.ZOBZ8V2YME5YOYZR]{&#x1F981; Lionized} for 10 minutes instead.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You regain all spent @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE]{&#x2728; Flair} points when you finish a long rest.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Bard", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Rogues' Gallery", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/death/skull-trio-badge-purple.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Everyone loves a good villain, and you've got no shortage of them. When a @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.WHN3T2G6R8HUKOQX]{&#x1F9FF; Villainized} creature within 60ft of you is reduced to 0 hit points or killed, you can use your reaction to make another creature you can see within 60ft of you @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.WHN3T2G6R8HUKOQX]{&#x1F9FF; Villainized} for 1 minute. <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If you don't take this reaction, then you do not need to have or spend any @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE]{&#x2728; Flair} points the first time you use the @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.018XFM2VDH6HIHL0]{Vilify} minor action within the next minute.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "novice"}, "requirements": "Bard", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "O9XP2FKIHU39PPPC", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Role Reversal", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/intimidation-impressing.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As a minor action you can spend 1 @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE]{&amp;#x2728; Flair}&nbsp;point to target a creature within 30ft of you that you can see with one of the following effects:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Glorify: </strong>The target becomes @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.ZOBZ8V2YME5YOYZR]{&amp;#x1F981; Lionized}&nbsp;for 10 minutes.</p><p><br /><strong>Vilify:</strong> The target becomes @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.WHN3T2G6R8HUKOQX]{&amp;#x1F9FF; Villainized}&nbsp;for 1 minute.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Bard", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "018XFM2VDH6HIHL0", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Share the Spotlight", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/targeting/target-glowing-yellow.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Somebody's got to play the lead role - why shouldn't it be you? Whenever you cause a creature to become @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.ZOBZ8V2YME5YOYZR]{&#x1F981; Lionized}, you can choose to become @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.ZOBZ8V2YME5YOYZR]{&#x1F981; Lionized} yourself for the same duration.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "novice"}, "requirements": "Bard", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "XVWY4BL8VIERNETM", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Spellcasting (Bard)", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/symbols/rune-sigil-black-pink.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As one who uses arcane means to bend this world to your will with magic, you have in your possession a spell book, or grimoire if you will.  And it is the guidebook to reconstructing your reality.</p><h4><strong>Cantrips</strong></h4><p>Upon gaining your 1st level of Bard, you know two Cantrips from the Bard&rsquo;s spell list.  You will learn additional Cantrips as you advance in the Bard class.  You gain an additional Cantrip when you hit Adept Bard, and then another at Expert Bard.</p><h4><strong>Spells at 1st Level</strong></h4><p>A Bard at 1st level knows four level 1 spells of their choice from the Bard&rsquo;s spell list.</p><h4><strong>Casting Spells</strong></h4><p>A Bard, like all spellcasters, expends Mana to cast spells (expanded upon in the Mana section of <strong>&ldquo;Chapter 9: Magic & Spellcasting&rdquo;</strong>).  As well, you regain your Mana fully on a long rest, and partially on a short rest.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You can cast any Bard spells you have learned.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(Note: To figure out how many and what spells you know, reference the <b>Spells at 1st Level</b> above this section, and if needed, the <b>Learning Spells at Higher Levels</b> section in the @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.classes.MGOXKZCFR46MSF08]{Bard} Class.)</p><h4><strong>Spellcasting Ability</strong></h4><p>Given that your magic is brought to life through rousing performances, Presence is the spellcasting ability for a Bard.  This means that your Presence modifier comes into play when setting the DC for your Bard spells and when making an attack with one.</p><ul><li><i>Spell Save DC:</i> 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Presence modifier</li><li><i>Spell Attack Modifier:</i> your proficiency bonus + your Presence modifier</li></ul><h4><strong>Ritual Casting</strong></h4><p>You can cast a Bard spell as a Ritual if that spell has the Ritual tag and you have learned the spell.</p><h4><strong>Spellcasting Focus</strong></h4><p>You may use an arcane focus, a specialized item used for casting, as a spellcasting focus for casting your Bard spells, or a musical instrument you are proficient with.  Spellcasting focuses allow spells to be cast without needing the material components, but does not replace material components that have a cost or are said to be used up by the spell.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Bard", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "ZD6YNR1QX0H3BJPP", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Bard Spells", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-runed-white.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>1st level Bards get access to Bardic Magic, which consists of 1st through 7th level spells.  However, you do not have access to all of them right away.  These spell levels become accessible as follows:</p><p><i>Bard Spell Levels</i></p><table><tr><th>Spell Level</th><th>Unlock Requirements</th></tr><tr><td>Level 1 Spells</td><td>1st Level Bard.</td></tr><tr><td>Level 2 Spells</td><td>2nd Level Bard;<br>3rd Level Overall.</td></tr><tr><td>Level 3 Spells</td><td>3rd Level Bard;<br>5th Level Overall<br>(At least 4 of these levels must be in Spellcaster classes).</td></tr><tr><td>Level 4 Spells</td><td>4th Level Bard;<br>7th Level Overall<br>(At least 6 of these levels must be in Spellcaster classes).</td></tr><tr><td>Level 5 Spells</td><td>5th Level Bard;<br>9th Level Overall<br>(At least 8 of these levels must be in Spellcaster classes).</td></tr><tr><td>Level 6 Spells</td><td>6th Level Bard;<br>11th Level Overall<br>(At least 10 of these levels must be in Spellcaster classes).</td></tr><tr><td>Level 7 Spells</td><td>7th Level Bard;<br>13th Level Overall<br>(At least 12 of these levels must be in Spellcaster classes).</td></tr></table>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Bard", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "XTPYQVEB8Y00E344", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Timely Backup", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/time/hourglass-tilted-glowing-gold.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "As a desperate action, you can move to any creature that is no more than half your movement speed away from you and use the <b>Assist</b> action on it. Unlike other desperate actions, you can use this ability to interrupt the desperate actions of willing creatures.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Unfortunately, onlookers may become annoyed if you keep inserting yourself into pivotal moments in this way. Each time you use this ability again before your next short rest, become @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.WHN3T2G6R8HUKOQX]{&#x1F9FF; Villainized} until the end of your next turn. You only suffer from the baseline effects of being villainized, not any other abilities you have that would apply to creatures you've villainized.", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Must have a Bard Adept Ability", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "0QAS4D8W7N209D20", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Beseech Providence", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/people/cleric-orange.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You are no stranger to setting an example of your faith, both in your deeds and in your words. You have advantage on Presence (Persuasion) checks made to implore someone to carry out a selfless act that is at most inconvenient to them (such as helping a neighbor rebuild their shed or donating a small amount to a starving creature).</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "background", "subtype": ""}, "requirements": "Early Devotee", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": "Background Features", "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "CZKRUMYCK6X1L5WN", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Choose Your Battles", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/people/infantry-army.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>The supreme art of war is to subdue the enemy without fighting. You have advantage on Presence (Intimidation) checks made to convince others to back down from a fight with you.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "background", "subtype": ""}, "requirements": "Early Militant", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": "Background Features", "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "QJK4VRMK8IZWD41C", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Eye for Quality", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/trades/textiles-cloth-dye-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You are skilled at appraising any non-magical object that could be crafted by a trade you are proficient with. You have advantage on checks to determine the base price of these crafts and identify forgeries.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "background", "subtype": ""}, "requirements": "Early Artisan", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": "Background Features", "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "5Z5KEPS9RQKUVCPC", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Institutional Sway", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/treasure/broach-crown-gold.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your insignia and general air distinguish you from the unwashed masses, making bureaucrats and authority figures less likely to dismiss your concerns. Should you need to arrange an audience or appointment, you have advantage on Presence (Persuasion) checks to do so.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "background", "subtype": ""}, "requirements": "Early Aristocrat", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": "Background Features", "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "2BWN854LL0WQ39J3", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Know the Ropes", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/settlement/ship.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You are no stranger to the workings of a ship. You can easily negotiate passage on a ship for you and your companions in exchange for labor during the voyage, provided the ship has enough excess capacity to accommodate you. Should the crew require convincing, you have advantage on the associated Presence (Persuasion) checks.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "background", "subtype": ""}, "requirements": "Early Sailor", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": "Background Features", "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "6S8K0D2XXAKPWE4J", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Bloopers", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/time/arrows-circling-pink.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Whenever you witness a creature within 30 feet of you that is @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.ZOBZ8V2YME5YOYZR]{&#x1F981; Lionized} fail an attack roll or check, you can use your reaction to make it roll again. On a success, it succeeds in its goal thanks to sheer luck, an improbable coincidence, or some other comically convoluted means.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Once you cause a creature to succeed using this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a rest or unless you spend a @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE]{&#x2728; Flair} point as part of the reaction. The @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE]{&#x2728; Flair} point is refunded if the creature fails the reroll.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Bard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "YNYRG1OSHNZ1HDC1", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "People Person", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When trying to get a laugh out of a crowd, you've found it helps to know a bit about their experiences and values. You gain proficiency in Intelligence (Culture).</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Bard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "UT2MT6HXQ4PUJKCF", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Prop Weapons", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/tools/cooking/fork-steel-brown.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your unexpected and exaggerated style of combat often catches opponents off guard. You are proficient with improvised weapons. Whenever you make an improvised weapon attack, you can use your Presence modifier in place of Strength or Dexterity for the attack and damage roll. When determining the damage of an improvised weapon, you can use 1d6 in place of its normal damage die, or 1d8 if you hold the object with two hands. If an improvised weapon you are wielding breaks as a result of hitting a creature, the attack deals an additional 1d4 damage.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Bard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "TJ4VKZYFH31W9X3V", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Self-Insert", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/movement/figure-running-gray.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You're no stranger to physical forms of comedy, and know how best to play up a tumble to elicit concerned gasps and relieved laughs from your audience and even yourself, manifesting this internal comedic logic to shield you from the worst of it. Whenever you use a desperate action <b>Saving a Target</b> to comically get in the way of the attack, you have resistance to the attack's damage.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If the damage you suffer (after any reductions) equal or exceeds your character level, gain a @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE]{&#x2728; Flair} point.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Bard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "7RD3VKTZ5NAWVBRS", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Slapstick", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/wood/furniture-stool-brown.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Any time you would make a melee weapon attack, you can replace it with an attempt to <strong>Shove</strong> or <strong>Trip</strong> a target, not just when taking the Attack action. While you have a free hand, you can use your minor action to <strong>Shove</strong> or <strong>Trip</strong> a creature. Creatures you successfully <strong>Trip</strong> take 1d6 bludgeoning damage when they hit the ground.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Finally, when you are initiating or resisting an attempt to <strong>Shove</strong> or <strong>Trip</strong>, you can make a Presence (Perform) check in place of the normal check.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Bard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "OS4PU32OTOKG859U", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Theme: Levity", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/control/mouth-smile-deception-purple.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your art is fueled by the levity that comes with bewilderment, peculiarity, and irony. Whenever a creature that you can see within 60ft of you rolls a natural 1 on an attack roll or skill check, gain 1 @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE]{&#x2728; Flair} point.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You can only benefit from one Theme ability at a time. If you have multiple Theme abilities, you can change which one is active when you finish a rest and any time you spend a @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE]{&#x2728; Flair} point on an ability.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Bard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "XS4831HQBSH7W2M4", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Boarding Party", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/settlement/ship.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You&rsquo;re experienced at using ranged weaponry both at a distance and in the thick of a fray. Your ranged attacks no longer suffer disadvantage as a result of targeting a creature that is within 5 feet of you or prone.</p><p>Additionally, you can use your minor action to reload a weapon with the Loading property between attacks.</p><p>You learn the following Gambit: @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.L65XCJ63D6V6QUVJ]{Gambit: Shot Across the Bow}</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "W6WA5QK7MVTV83IS", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Contingency Plan", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/tools/navigation/map-marked-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Good luck only ever lasts so long. As a corsair, you&rsquo;re no stranger to cutthroats and thieves, and you&rsquo;re always waiting for the other boot to drop.&nbsp;</p><p>Whenever you are <strong>Surprised</strong>, you can still choose to do one of the following on your first turn of combat:</p><ul><li>Take an Action.</li><li>Move and take a Minor Action.</li><li>Gain temporary hit points equal to your level as a Non-Action.</li></ul><p>You also learn the following Gambits:&nbsp;@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.YUAJX59ZHM417PCB]{Gambit: Shake a Leg}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.150EJLYVPMDY2VLI]{Gambit: Loose Cannon}</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "EW5EDFT4VENBU9QJ", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Dead Men Tell No Tales", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/documents/document-symbol-skull-tan.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You&rsquo;re well-traveled and accustomed to conversing with parties on less than the most cooperative of terms. In that time you&rsquo;ve picked up a knack for &ldquo;putting things into perspective&rdquo;. You gain proficiency in Presence (Intimidation) or the Vehicle Trade.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "HLOE5LYM9Y1M9U58", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Gambit: Avast, Me Hearties!", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><strong>Gambit: Avast, Me Hearties!</strong></p><p><em>Cost: 1 Panache</em></p><p>As a minor action you can shout words of encouragement at a creature within 60 feet that can hear you. Spend one Panache dice to roll it and grant the creature temporary hit points equal to the number rolled.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "MQ87LWRH52O6XSGZ", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Gambit: Loose Cannon", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><strong>Gambit: Loose Cannon</strong></p><p><em>Cost: X Panache</em></p><p>Whenever you hit with an attack but are unable to use your Sneak Attack, you can choose to expend any number of Panache Dice to roll and add them to the attack&rsquo;s damage.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "150EJLYVPMDY2VLI", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Gambit: Scallywag", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><strong>Gambit: Scallywag</strong></p><p><em>Cost: 1 Panache</em></p><p>When you make a Presence (Intimidation) or Presence (Deception) check but before learning whether you succeed or fail, you can expend a single Panache Die to roll it and add it to the result.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "Y26KXC52QC1Z8Z4L", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Gambit: Getting Yer Sea Legs", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><strong>Gambit: Getting Yer Sea Legs</strong></p><p><em>Cost: 1 Panache</em></p><p>When you make a check to climb or avoid being knocked @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.RK3DF56CKMQUV6DM]{Prone} but before learning whether you succeed or fail, you can expend a single Panache Die to roll it and add it to the result.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "0LCC8YZ2VZB77YR9", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Gambit: Shake a Leg", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><strong>Gambit: Shake a Leg</strong></p><p><em>Cost: 1 Panache</em></p><p>Whenever you roll initiative and are not <strong>Surprised</strong>, you can expend a single Panache Die to roll it and add it to the result.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "YUAJX59ZHM417PCB", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Gambit: Shot Across the Bow", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><strong>Gambit: Shot Across the Bow</strong></p><p><em>Cost: 1 Panache</em></p><p>When you miss a creature with a ranged attack that would have been eligible for Sneak Attack, you can expend your use of Sneak Attack this turn and one Panache Die to turn the attack into a warning shot. The creature must succeed on a Wisdom (Save) Check against your Sneak Attack DC or take psychic damage equal to a roll of the Panache Die and become @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.UK95BQ45TGSD5Q3V]{Frightened} of you until the end of its next turn. A creature that would be reduced to 0 hit points by this damage faints instead, dropping to 1 hit point and falling @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.9KB959MRZ0H4IT4C]{Unconscious} for 1 minute.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "L65XCJ63D6V6QUVJ", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Gambit: Weigh Anchor", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><strong>Gambit: Weigh Anchor</strong></p><p><em>Cost: 1 Panache</em></p><p>To use this gambit, you must be holding a rope with an attached grappling hook. As a minor action, or as part of the Dash action, you can expend one Panache Dice to secure the rope to any protrusion above you (such as a tree branch, rock outcropping, pole, or chandelier) that is within the rope&rsquo;s length from you. You can alternatively attempt to secure it to a flying creature, however the creature can make a Dexterity (Save) Check versus your Sneak Attack DC to avoid it. You can use your action while touching a rope you secured with this ability to retrieve it and the attached grappling hook.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "OB8YW767NKUR0TXY", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Panache", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As a corsair, your effectiveness hinges upon taking bold risks to gain the upper hand. These feats of daring-do are represented by your Panache Dice, which are d6. You start with one Panache Die, and can hold up to a maximum of 1 + your Proficiency Bonus Panache Dice at a time. When you finish a long rest, you lose any unused Panache Dice and then gain one.</p><p>Gaining more Panache Dice to use requires taking risks. You can gain them in the following ways:</p><ul><li>Whenever you activate your Sneak Attack ability, you can choose to forgo up to half of your sneak attack dice in order to gain a Panache Die for each Sneak Attack die you sacrifice.</li><li>Before rolling a skill check you are proficient in for a non-trivial task, you can choose to take a penalty equal to your proficiency bonus in order to gain a Panache Die. This penalty is static and not increased by multipliers to your proficiency bonus, such as the Multi-Talented ability.</li></ul><p>You can use your Panache dice to fuel special abilities, called Corsair Gambits. You know one Gambit called <em>Scallywag</em>, detailed below, and can add new ones to your roster by taking the Corsair ability associated with each of them.</p><p><strong>Growth:</strong> Your Panache Die increases in size at each growth level, becoming a d8 at 5th level, d10 at 11th level, and d12 at 17th level.</p><p>You learn the following Gambit: @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.Y26KXC52QC1Z8Z4L]{Gambit: Scallywag}</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "EDSSCUMXYUHNCQ9F", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Rakish Charm", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/materials/feather-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your daring and bombastic ploys have a penchant to amaze onlookers.</p><p>Once per turn, when you perform a Gambit you can force one creature that saw it to make a Wisdom (Save) Check versus your Sneak Attack DC. Creatures with an Intelligence score of less than 3 automatically succeed.</p><p>On a failed save, the creature is @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.KJXJ0T5RPNC51N4V]{Charmed} by you until the end of its next turn. While a creature is @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.KJXJ0T5RPNC51N4V]{Charmed} in this way, its action can only be used to take the Disengage, Self-Defense, or Hide action. Once you charm a creature with this ability, that creature can&rsquo;t be @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.KJXJ0T5RPNC51N4V]{Charmed} by it again until you finish a long rest.</p><p>Whenever a creature fails its save against this ability, regardless of whether it can be @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.KJXJ0T5RPNC51N4V]{Charmed} or not, you gain advantage on the first Presence check directed at it within the next minute.</p><p>You also learn the following Gambit: @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.MQ87LWRH52O6XSGZ]{Gambit: Avast, Me Hearties!}</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "LYCMR7TCA8JCT44F", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Rigged Fight", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/tools/nautical/rope-line-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Whenever you land within 5 feet of a creature after swinging at least 10 feet on a dangling rope or chain, you gain advantage on your first attack roll against the creature this turn.</p><p>You also learn the following Gambits:&nbsp;@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.OB8YW767NKUR0TXY]{Gambit: Weigh Anchor}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.0LCC8YZ2VZB77YR9]{Gambit: Getting Yer Sea Legs}</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "OVP7QML1V8RHMWEZ", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Hungering Shadows", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/mammals/wolf-shadow-black.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>Unlock: </em>When you reach 6th level overall you may take the ability below.</p><p>Your @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.QVIXYJFEAOXHF2SW]{Dread Blade} cantrip ignores resistance to necrotic damage, and creatures that are immune to necrotic damage take half damage from it on a hit.</p><p>Additionally, over the course of a rest you can perform a ritual to merge a magical melee weapon with your shadow. At the end of the rest the weapon disappears and you attune to it, even if the item doesn&rsquo;t require attunement. While you have a weapon merged with your shadow, weapons created by your @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.QVIXYJFEAOXHF2SW]{Dread Blade} cantrip inherit all of the merged weapon&rsquo;s magical properties. If the weapon has charges or limited use abilities, track their expenditure as a single pool&mdash;summoning your @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.QVIXYJFEAOXHF2SW]{Dread Blade} multiple times does not grant extra uses of them. Creatures that closely inspect your shadow will notice that it appears to be holding the weapon while your @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.QVIXYJFEAOXHF2SW]{Dread Blade} isn&rsquo;t summoned or is banished.</p><p>A weapon merged with your shadow reappears a foot away from you when you die, your attunement to it ends, or you choose to merge a different weapon with your shadow. You can choose to end your attunement with a merged weapon over a rest.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "3rd level overall and have at least one level each in a Martial and Spellcaster class", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "5Y5UKK5OB00AYMHG", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Loyal Weapon", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/death/weapon-sword-skull-purple.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>The @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.QVIXYJFEAOXHF2SW]{Dread Blade} cantrip no longer requires concentration, and its duration is increased 8 to hours. The spell ends early if you cast it again. For the duration of the spell, you can banish and resummon the blade in place of sheathing or drawing a weapon.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "3rd level overall and have at least one level each in a Martial and Spellcaster class", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "WXAA4GO3QQKD1H7M", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "One Foot in the Grave", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/settlement/graveyard-tombstone-night.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have resistance to necrotic damage. You also have advantage on Save Checks made to resist any effect that would reduce your maximum hit points.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "3rd level overall and have at least one level each in a Martial and Spellcaster class", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "GJSBBBEWC3QHE19Y", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Reaper", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/weapons/sickles/scythe-curved-steel.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You gain proficiency with scythes. Whenever you cast the @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.QVIXYJFEAOXHF2SW]{Dread Blade} cantrip you can create a scythe with a damage die of 1d8 necrotic and the added trait <strong>Reach</strong>.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "3rd level overall and have at least one level each in a Martial and Spellcaster class", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "VP1MJ4K008E0P5QE", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Thanatophobia", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/death/skull-energy-light-purple.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Each time you hit a creature with an attack using your @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.QVIXYJFEAOXHF2SW]{Dread Blade}, you can spend 1 mana to attempt to instill fear in it. The creature must succeed on a Wisdom (Save) Check versus your spell save DC or become @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.UK95BQ45TGSD5Q3V]{Frightened} of you until the end of its next turn. A creature that succeeds on its save is immune to this ability until the start of your next turn.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "3rd level overall and have at least one level each in a Martial and Spellcaster class", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "H5SWPCUEGNVFEPPT", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Tools of the Harvest", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/trades/farming-sickle-harvest-wheat.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You learn the @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.QVIXYJFEAOXHF2SW]{Dread Blade} cantrip, and Intelligence, Wisdom, or Presence is your spellcasting attribute for it.</p><p>If you already knew the @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.QVIXYJFEAOXHF2SW]{Dread Blade} cantrip before selecting this Archetype or later learn it from another source, you instead gain proficiency with one of the following: daggers, sickles, shortswords, hatchets.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "3rd level overall and have at least one level each in a Martial and Spellcaster class", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "5GKWWIQFXU0YBEWB", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "The Best Defense", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/melee/shield-block-bash-yellow.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>They say the best defense is a good offense. Well, who's to say your shield can't provide both.</p><p>You treat shields you wield as martial melee weapons with a damage die of 1d6 bludgeoning damage. Shields that lack the <b>Heavy</b> trait gain the trait <b>Thrown (20/60)</b>. Shields with the <b>Heavy</b> or <b>Two-Handed</b> trait gain an additional trait <b>Versatile (1d8)</b>.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Fighter Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "UN7U2EJY5GRE4EB6", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Heads Up", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/tools/instruments/megaphone.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When you roll initiative and are not <b>Surprised</b>, you can quickly coordinate with one of your allies to prepare for the coming danger. After initiative has been rolled but before the first turn of combat, you can choose to immediately move adjacent to an allied creature that is reachable with half of your movement speed. If the chosen creature is ahead of you in the initiative order, move yourself to the spot immediately after it in the initiative order. Otherwise, move the creature to the spot immediately before you in the initiative order.</p><p>Subtract any movement used by this ability from the movement available to you on your first turn of combat. You can't use this ability on a creature that has already used or been the target of another copy of this ability in this combat.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Fighter Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "HS30FINEX9HB4RZE", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Heroic Adrenaline", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/holy/barrier-shield-winged-cross.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>Unlock: </em>When you reach 6th level overall and have the ability <i>Adrenaline</i> you may take the ability below.</p><p>Seeing others in peril stirs you to action and pushes you beyond your limits. Whenever you Size-Up an ally and learn that they are closest to \u00c2\u00bc Hit Points remaining or less, you can choose to regain an expended use of your <i>Adrenaline</i> ability. If you do, you can't use this ability on that same ally again until you finish a long rest.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Fighter Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "N5DFPGT4NAZQ3RM9", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Retribution", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/tools/hand/scale-balances-merchant-brown.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Creatures within your weapon's reach provoke an attack of opportunity from you when they attack a creature other than you, unless the creature they are attacking also has this ability. If you hit with this attack of opportunity, your target's victim also gains 1d4 temporary hit points.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Fighter Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "G5GV21SNLQ4Q8K8C", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Fighting Stance: Bodyguard", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/equipment/shield/heater-crystal-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><i>Requirement:</i> A shield, with or without a weapon in your other hand.</p><hr><p>You step closer to your ward, holding your shield out so that it protects both of you. Surveying the field for threats they might not even see, you prepare yourself to do anything to keep the heat off of them.</p><hr><u>Pros</u><p><b>Selfless Defense</b><ul><li>In addition to the normal methods, you can enter this stance at the end of a Self-Defense action or as a reaction to a creature ending its turn within 5 feet of you.</li></ul><b>Guardian</b><ul><li>One creature of your choice also gains the AC bonus of a single shield you are wielding while they are within 5 feet of you. A creature that is wielding a shield of its own does not gain this bonus.</li></ul><b>Got Your Back</b><ul><li>When an ally within 5 feet moves, you can use your Reaction to move with them up to your maximum movement speed.</li></ul></p><hr><u>Cons</u><p><b>On Defense</b><ul><li>Creatures do not provoke Attacks of Opportunity from you when leaving your weapon range.</li></ul><b>Divided Protection</b><ul><li>You suffer a -1 penalty to your AC</li></ul></p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "stance"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "L7C1Z21RZCX2NKTL", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Fighting Stance: Decoy", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/settlement/target-dummy.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><i>Requirement:</i> Not wielding a shield and not @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.YE63H7VLOHW7NFHO]{Invisible}. You can wield other weapons while in this stance as long as the requirements remain met.</p><hr><p>Squaring up your shoulders and standing boldly in clear view, you feign an opening in your defenses while confidently eyeing your foes, as if daring them to make the first strike. Getting through your enemy's armor will be trivial once your attitude has gotten under their skin.</p><hr><u>Pros</u><p><b>Insult to Injury</b><ul><li>Your weapon and unarmed attacks deal an additional 1d4 psychic damage. The size of this damage die cannot be increased or decreased.</li></ul><b>Undaunted</b><ul><li>Creatures with the @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.Y822OUCDEPAG0HS8]{Frenzied} condition do not add their Wisdom (Instinct) modifier to attack and damage rolls targeting you.</li></ul><b>Taunt</b><ul><li>As a minor action, you can attempt to goad a creature within 20 feet into a duel with you. They must make a Wisdom (Save) check of DC 8 + Your Presence Modifier + Your Proficiency Bonus. On a failure, they become @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.Y822OUCDEPAG0HS8]{Frenzied} until the end of their next turn. The condition ends early if the creature can no longer see you or you move far enough away that the creature could not reach you without using the Dash action.</li><ul><li>If you activate this ability on a target after hitting them with at least one weapon attack in the same turn, the target suffers a -2 penalty to their Save check.</li></ul><li>Creatures @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.Y822OUCDEPAG0HS8]{Frenzied} by this ability:</li><ul><li>Always consider you the nearest target, even if other creatures are closer.</li><li>Can continue to concentrate on spells, but have disadvantage on checks to maintain concentration.</li><li>May still cast spells, but only if the spell involves making one or more attacks against you and no other creatures. Alternatively, the creature may target themself or an object with a spell if it would allow them to make an attack against you during the same turn it was cast.</li></ul></ul><b>That All You've Got?</b><ul><li>After you suffer bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing damage, you can use your reaction to gain resistance to one of the listed damage types you just suffered for all subsequent attacks and effects, lasting until the start of your next turn.</li></ul></p><hr><u>Cons</u><p><b>Chip on Your Shoulder</b><ul><li>Your AC is reduced by 2.  If you are wearing Heavy armor, your AC is reduced by 3 instead.</li><li>Attacks of Opportunity have advantage against you.</li></ul><b>Inflated Ego</b><ul><li>Taking a Desperate Action causes you to immediately leave this stance before resolving the action.</li></ul><b>Obvious Target</b><ul><li>You automatically lose Dexterity (Stealth) contests against other creatures' Wisdom (Perception) or Awareness.</li></ul></p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "stance"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "TGJ46BXWJNNZTG8R", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Fighting Stance: Fortress", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/gaming/chess-rook-gray.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><i>Requirement:</i> Heavy armor or a shield with the Heavy trait. You can wield other weapons while in this stance as long as the requirements remain met.</p><hr><p>You lean into the weight and heft of your armor or shield, carefully placing your feet and shoring up your balance to make any attempt to undermine you an uphill battle. You are a living wall of steel.</p><hr><u>Pros</u><p><b>Impervious</b><ul><li>You can reduce Bludgeoning, Slashing, and Piercing damage you take by an amount equal to your proficiency bonus.</li></ul><b>Immovable Object</b><ul><li>You have advantage on checks made to avoid being moved or knocked prone.</li><li>Whenever you win a contested skill check to avoid being shoved, tripped, or grappled, you can immediately push your opponent 5 ft in any direction if they are no more than one size larger than you</li></ul></p><hr><u>Cons</u><p><b>Weighed Down</b><ul><li>Your movement speed is halved.</li><li>You have disadvantage on Dexterity (save) checks.</li></ul><b>Obstructed Vision</b><ul><li>You have disadvantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks relying on sight.</li></ul><b>Limited Defense</b><ul><li>If you leave this stance, you cannot re-enter this stance this turn.</li></ul></p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "stance"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "S8BIHKJPHEGR910P", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Fighting Stance: Rebound", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/light/beam-impact-deflect-teal.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><i>Requirement:</i> A Buckler or a bludgeoning weapon with the Thrown trait and no other weapons.</p><hr><p>You grip your throwing implement and wind back your arm, ready to hurl the mass towards an approaching foe. While blunt throwing weapons might not have the best aerodynamics, at this distance they pack enough punch to send attackers reeling back the way they came.</p><hr><u>Pros</u><p><b>Jumbo Discus</b><ul><li>Bucklers you wield gain the <b>Thrown (20/60)</b> trait.</li></ul><b>Go for Gold</b><ul><li>As an action, you can make a single thrown weapon attack that has advantage within its normal range and suffers no disadvantage from going beyond its normal range. Attacks that exceed the maximum range still miss.</li></ul><b>Rebound</b><ul><li>After making an attack with a thrown weapon, it bounces back towards you.</li><ul><li>If the attack hits, the weapon rebounds directly to you and you catch it.</li><li>If the attack misses, it bounces harmlessly and lands in a random space within 5 ft of you.</li></ul></ul><b>Confounding Blows</b><ul><li>When you hit a creature with your weapon, they have disadvantage on the first weapon attack they make before the end of their next turn.</li></ul><b>Bank Shot</b><ul><li>When you score a critical hit with a thrown weapon, you can choose to have it bounce towards another target instead of immediately returning. Make an attack with advantage against a different creature within the weapon's range from the current target. The weapon still returns after the attack chain ends, as long as there was no <b>Catastrophic Miss</b>.</li></ul></p><hr><u>Cons</u><p><b>Catastrophic Miss</b><ul><li>Upon critically failing a thrown weapon attack, the weapon does not return to you and instead flies 20ft past the target before hitting the ground.</li><li>Attacks beyond a weapon's maximum range also suffer a <b>Catastrophic Miss</b>.</li></ul><b>Conservation of Momentum</b><ul><li>The normal and maximum ranges of thrown weapons are halved.</li></ul></p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "stance"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "0FNB61M34QI8Q8AT", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Fighting Stance: Gladiator", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/equipment/shield/heater-steel-sword-yellow-black.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You learn 1 fighting stance from the following list.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;When you can choose a new Fighting Stance as part of leveling up, you can choose from one of these Fighting Stances as well.<br><br><u><i>Fighting Stance List: Defender</i></u><br>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.L7C1Z21RZCX2NKTL]{Bodyguard Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.S8BIHKJPHEGR910P]{Fortress Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.0FNB61M34QI8Q8AT]{Rebound Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.TGJ46BXWJNNZTG8R]{Decoy Stance}</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Must have the Fighter Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "5A7HOEBVANPTZD28", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Vigilant", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/settlement/watchtower-moonlit-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You are always on alert, waiting for the other shoe to drop. You gain proficiency in Wisdom (Perception).</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Fighter Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "IJ4DSNSC69UF86HZ", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Covetous Defiance", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/equipment/chest/breastplate-layered-gold.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You know to keep your friends close, your enemies closer, and your hoard closest of all. You gain a bonus to your maximum hit points based on the magic items you are attuned to at any given moment. The bonus for each item is determined by its rarity, as follows:</p><ul><li>Common: +1 maximum hit points.</li><li>Uncommon: +3 maximum hit points.</li><li>Rare: +5 maximum hit points.</li><li>Very Rare: +7 maximum hit points.</li><li>Legendary: +10 maximum hit points.</li><li>Artifact: +10 maximum hit points, and your maximum rest dice for Cleric increases by 1.</li></ul><p>Additionally, while you have all of your attunement slots filled you also gain a +1 bonus to all save checks.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Dragon Dominion", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "D1GJLP59RK0A613P", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Miracles of Draconic Transubstantiation", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/abilities/dragon-ice-breath-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>Unlock: </em>When you reach 6th level overall you may take the ability below</p><p>In the moments when your faith comes into complete clarity, you find the will to temporarily transcend the limits of your physical form, reshaping it to embody one or more traits associated with dragons of your affinity.</p><p>The <strong>Transformation Miracles</strong> below are added to your pool of Miracle options. Each of these miracles lasts until you finish a long rest, and the number of Transformation Miracles you can have active at once cannot exceed your Proficiency Bonus. Some of the miracles can be activated a second time in order to upgrade its effects. Transformation Miracles upgraded in this way count as two active Transformation Miracles. If you activate a Transformation Miracle while you are at the limit, you must choose another active one to downgrade or end.</p><ul><li><strong>Armatura Draconis: </strong>Your skin is covered with dragon scales. Your AC can&rsquo;t be less than 16, regardless of what armor you&rsquo;re wearing, and you gain resistance to the damage type of your Elemental Affinity.&nbsp;<ul><li>Activating this miracle again grants immunity to the damage type of your Elemental Affinity.</li></ul></li></ul><ul><li><strong>Irae Draconis:</strong> You sprout a set of claws on each of your hands and a formidable dragon tail. The claws are natural weapons with a damage die of 1d6 slashing damage and have the Finesse and Light properties. The tail is a natural weapon with a damage die of 2d6 bludgeoning damage and Reach property, and while you are Medium or larger it also gains the Heavy property.<ul><li>Activating this Miracle again gives you the following ability: As a Minor Action, you can make a tail attack.</li></ul></li></ul><ul><li><strong>Potentia Draconis:</strong> Ridges emerge from your back as your stature bulks and lengthens. Your size increases by one category, unless you are already Large or bigger, and you have advantage on Strength checks. Your equipment grows with you so long as it is on your person.&nbsp;<ul><li>Activating this Miracle again grants an additional 5 feet of reach to all of your melee attacks and spells with a range of Touch.</li></ul></li></ul><ul><li><strong>Spiritus Draconis:</strong> Your head morphs to resemble that of a dragon, granting you the following ability: As an Action, you can spend 1 @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die and exhale destructive power. Each creature in a 15 ft cone originating from you must succeed on a Dexterity (Save) check versus your Cleric Spell Save DC or take 3d6 damage in the damage type of your Elemental Affinity. On a successful save, a creature takes half damage.<ul><li>Activating this miracle again increases the ability&rsquo;s damage to 4d6 and the size of the cone to 20ft.</li></ul></li></ul><ul><li><strong>Volatus Draconis: </strong>You manifest a pair of dragon&rsquo;s wings, granting you a flying speed equal to your walking speed.&nbsp;<ul><li>Activating this Miracle again gives you the following ability: Until the miracle ends you can beat your wings as an Action and attempt to shove every creature that is within 5 feet of you. Creatures that fail are pushed an additional 5 feet and take 1d6 bludgeoning damage.</li></ul></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Dragon Dominion", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "DF3V1QA5MH23X8LZ", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Elemental Affinity", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/reptiles/dragon-horned-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As part of becoming a cleric of the Dragon Dominion, you must choose one damage type to become your Elemental Affinity. Your choice of affinity will determine the damage type and spell options of other Dragon Dominion abilities.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Choose one of the following to be your Elemental Affinity: Acid, Cold, Fire, Lightning, or Poison.</em></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>You draw conviction from seeing the elemental power of your affinity made manifest in the world. Whenever you roll at least one set of doubles for damage that matches the type of your Elemental Affinity on a die that isn&rsquo;t a d4, you can gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die and activate the Mantras assigned to your <strong>Number of the Dragon</strong>. Triples or multiple sets of doubles do not grant any additional bonuses.</p><p>You can change your choice of affinity whenever you reach a growth level, replacing all abilities and spells granted by your old one. Once every 7 days, when you touch a living true dragon or permanent site of draconic worship, you can choose to change your affinity to the one most closely associated with the entity in question.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "UROYUWYQ5D1XOMRC", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Fearsome Presence", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/reptiles/dragon-horned-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You exude the awe and power of the dragons. You gain proficiency in Presence (Intimidation) if you were not already proficient in it, and you can speak, read, and write Draconic.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "BP376DKTF70JKEHV", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Hoarded Blessings", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/currency/coin-engraved-tail-gold.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>To better emulate the might of dragons, you have made a practice of collecting portions of the power that flows through you, sequestering them within your very being until the time is right to make a demonstration.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You have a <strong>Spiritual Hoard</strong>, which resets to 0 whenever you finish a long rest. Before applying the effects of a roll to determine healing given to a creature or damage dealt to a genuine adversary, you can choose to hoard a single rolled die. Add that die&rsquo;s result to your Spiritual Hoard, and then set the die to a 1. The affected die does not count towards effects that trigger upon rolling one or more of a specific number, such as Eikonic Numbers or Miracles.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;While the total of your Spiritual Hoard equals or exceeds 25, you can subtract 25 from it to trigger a Miracle as a non-action on your turn.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Dragon Dominion", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "JKVO726WWVKAVE2W", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Mantras of the Dragon", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/reptiles/dragon-horned-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When you learn this ability, the following Mantras are added to your list of available Mantras to choose from.&nbsp; However, these Mantras can only be associated with your <strong>Number of the Dragon</strong>.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>In addition, when this is unlocked, you can swap out 1 Mantra you know for another one.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><ul><li><strong>Suffer No Insult:</strong> Until the end of your next turn, attackers that hit you with melee attacks suffer 1d4 damage of your Elemental Affinity's type.</li><li><strong>Mine, All Mine:</strong> Coins with a total gp value equal to your proficiency bonus appear in a container you're carrying.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "CUTXVGMQ0RG5EE7O", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Number of the Dragon", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/reptiles/dragon-horned-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your Eikonic Number for the Dragon Dominion, known as your Number of the Dragon, is 16.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "T15IEHRWISA9JGIO", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Purloined Essence", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/abilities/dragon-breath-purple.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As a reaction to taking damage that matches your Elemental Affinity's type, you can spend your @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Dice to heal yourself for the total faith roll plus your Wisdom modifier. You can use this ability even if the initial damage was reduced to 0, for example as a result of resistance or immunity.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Dragon Dominion", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "4RLLUUNYF7O4NQJ6", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Dragon Dominion Spells", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/reptiles/dragon-horned-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><i>Spells without compendium links set up are still undergoing approval</i></p><p>Clerics of the Dragon Dominion learn the following spells once able to cast spells of that level.&nbsp; These spells are always prepared and don&rsquo;t count against your prepared spell amount.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>If a dominion spell is not listed as a Cleric spell, it nonetheless counts as a Cleric spell for you.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p><em>Dragon Dominion Spells</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Able to Cast</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Dominion Spells</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1st Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p><em>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-1.DR1S6TA7ZZHXVKVY]{Menacing Visage},</em> and the additional spell of your Elemental Affinity.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2nd Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p><em>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-2.H12OZBL02CSFQX6L]{Dragon&rsquo;s Breath},</em> and the additional spell of your Elemental Affinity.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>3rd Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p><em>Sprout Wings*,</em> and the additional spell of your Elemental Affinity.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>4th Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p><em>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-4.YL8USCAX1ZTDKOA1]{Shapeshift},</em> and the additional spell of your Elemental Affinity.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>5th Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p><em>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-5.IGNKJCNA0BXYD1OT]{Unnatural Recovery},</em> and the additional spell of your Elemental Affinity.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Additional Spells by Affinity</em></p><style>table#affinity td{width:20%; max-width:20%; min-width:20%;} #affinity{min-width: 850px;}</style><table id='affinity'><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Able to Cast</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Acid Affinity</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Cold Affinity</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Fire Affinity</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Lightning Affinity</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Poison Affinity</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1st Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p><em>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-cantrips.MB7NWQ5H11LSIVV7]{Caustic Needle}</em></p></td><td><p><em>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.KH6D03TEJYZNA62N]{Deposition}</em></p></td><td><p><em>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.58I1UTE8ZV4CJ5W6]{Adherent Ember}</em></p></td><td><p><em>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-cantrips.0JWJ9J7A2AMSNDK0]{Jolt}</em></p></td><td><p><em>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.3L7I8DH0G63AX9B1]{Create Miasma}</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2nd Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p><em>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-level-1.93IZ61HQGJ91795Y]{Brittle Beam}</em></p></td><td><p><em>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-1.FBBZHRD9FHGJV2C4]{Hypothermia}</em></p></td><td><p><em>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-1.LO6PLV28RA6CBCLU]{Burst Into Flames}</em></p></td><td><p><em>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-level-1.37VLMG8DVH1QVCYM]{Charge Conduit}</em></p></td><td><p><em>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-1.N3BHT4QNPIDGVC6C]{Nocuous Bubble}</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>3rd Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-level-2.DV87F1MQUC5C59VW]{Corrosive Wash}</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-level-2.HVOF7QNI17K2O6C1]{Snowslide}</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-level-2.WR681XHI4K1RFFID]{Cauterize}</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-level-2.BNG42U9X3RWWFWXA]{Static Spark}</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-level-2.IGNXR8HBQZS1JVCY]{Ophidian Kiss}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>4th Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p><em>Astringent Bog*</em></p></td><td><p><em>Frigid Barrage*</em></p></td><td><p><em>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-3.7UWC00HNXCOL4GFI]{Fireball}</em></p></td><td><p><em>Wandering Storm*</em></p></td><td><p><em>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-3.TA1E58P8XATOBEQH]{Virulent Outbreak}</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>5th Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p><em>Acidic Wave*</em></p></td><td><p><em>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-4.H2RO4K8JLYTVNEXB]{Winter&rsquo;s Piercing Ray}</em></p></td><td><p><em>Burning Blood*</em></p></td><td><p><em>Pillars of Fulmination*</em></p></td><td><p><em>Neutralizing Venom*</em></p></td></tr></tbody></table>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "PF2GG3QRNRTNOXYS", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Ashen Drift", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/air/wind-stream-blue-gray.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>While your familiar is within 60 feet of you, you can spend 2 mana to teleport to an unoccupied space within 5 feet of it as a minor action.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "3rd level overall and have at least one level each in a Martial and Spellcaster class", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "6Q8NPXGTPOTSP2KO", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Fuel the Flames", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/fire/flame-burning-campfire-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>Unlock: </em>When you reach 6th level overall you may take the ability below.</p><p>Whenever an ember created by your @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.58I1UTE8ZV4CJ5W6]{Adherent Ember} cantrip detonates, gain temporary hit points equal to the number rolled on the detonation damage die, not including any modifiers or bonuses.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "3rd level overall and have at least one level each in a Martial and Spellcaster class", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "17T1JOINDUGBWTGS", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Kindled Companion", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/fire/projectile-smoke-swirl-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your familiar gains a bonus equal to your proficiency bonus to its AC, saving throws, attack rolls, and damage rolls of its attacks.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "3rd level overall and have at least one level each in a Martial and Spellcaster class", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "RZWY2QVJ74LA8RZ6", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Primordial Bond", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/fire/flame-burning-eye.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You learn the @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-level-1.TT94JMKOUYP2WM96]{Cojoin Familiar} spell. Familiars you create with this spell gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li>The familiar&rsquo;s attacks deal fire damage instead of the listed damage types.</li><li>The familiar is immune to fire damage.</li><li>The familiar&rsquo;s creature type is Elemental.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "3rd level overall and have at least one level each in a Martial and Spellcaster class", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "06UDKKP6BQGSGKF8", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Seeker's Knack", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/fire/flame-burning-campfire-smoke.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You learn the @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.58I1UTE8ZV4CJ5W6]{Adherent Ember} cantrip, and Intelligence, Wisdom, or Presence is your spellcasting attribute for it.</p><p>If you already knew the @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.58I1UTE8ZV4CJ5W6]{Adherent Ember} cantrip before selecting this Archetype or later learn it from another source, you instead gain proficiency with one of the following: sling, slingshot, or the Pathfinding Trade.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "3rd level overall and have at least one level each in a Martial and Spellcaster class", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "1P73PV63XRZZ06AX", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Smoldering Quiver", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/fire/projectile-arrow-fire-orange-yellow.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You gain proficiency with one of the following: shortbow, longbow, light crossbow, heavy crossbow, repeating crossbow.</p><p>Whenever you cast the @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.58I1UTE8ZV4CJ5W6]{Adherent Ember} cantrip, it creates 1d4 additional embers and you can choose to shape the embers into ammunition appropriate for any ranged weapon you are proficient with.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "3rd level overall and have at least one level each in a Martial and Spellcaster class", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "0XE5EBEOURNKXDWE", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Baleful Resistance", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/death/undead-ghosts-trio-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have resistance to necrotic damage.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "U2LZOAWTN9HEYR6F", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Cryptic Essence", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/magical/humanoid-giant-forest-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have advantage on save checks against spells that can only target humanoids.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "LH7JHOI6Q9N5ES88", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Chthonic Magic", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/death/skull-horned-goat-pentagram-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You know the @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.Q31B0A3FNPWP10MQ]{Prying Whispers} cantrip. When you reach 3rd level, you can cast the @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-1.DR1S6TA7ZZHXVKVY]{Menacing Visage} spell once with this trait and regain the ability to do so when you finish a long rest. When you reach 5th level, you can cast the @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-2.A0XHQ6VS7PDGN9FJ]{Cloak} spell once with this trait and regain the ability to do so when you finish a long rest. Intelligence, Wisdom, or Presence is your spellcasting attribute for it (chosen when you select this race).</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "T8FJEIROS5Z5B8TH", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Elysian Magic", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/holy/chalice-glowing-gold-water.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You know the @Compendium[undertaking.spells-cantrips.1UP8YL8Z33NMUI5P]{Minor Wonder} cantrip. When you reach 3rd level, you can cast the @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-1.MRQUPL1D078DKFR2]{No Reproach} spell once with this trait and regain the ability to do so when you finish a long rest. When you reach 5th level, you can cast the @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-2.YCQC074MGCT6R2NY]{Ultimatum} spell once with this trait and regain the ability to do so when you finish a long rest. Intelligence, Wisdom, or Presence is your spellcasting attribute for it (chosen when you select this race).</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "4VJ2G7YQ1FMRJWEX", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Empyrean Resistance", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/holy/barrier-shield-winged-cross.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have resistance to radiant damage.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "0Z0Q6FNI3460D9OW", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Healing Hands", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/life/heart-hand-gold-green-light.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As an action, you can touch a creature and cause it to regain a number of hit points equal to your level. Once you use this trait, you can't use it again until you finish a long rest.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "AHPJ6C17ALZ9WJ8G", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Omen of Fortune", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/control/buff-luck-fortune-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Whenever a creature you can see within 10 feet of you attempts a Presence skill check, you can use your reaction to add 1d4 to the roll. You can use this ability a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and regain all expended uses whenever you finish a long rest.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "WSK3MYKHHGFSAXNM", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Ominous Sight", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/perception/eye-ringed-glow-angry-large-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your darkvision is not impeded by magical darkness. When you are standing in dim light or darkness, your eyes faintly glow red if they are open and not hidden by illusion. While your eyes glow in this way, you have disadvantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks and advantage on Presence (Intimidation) checks.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "G0FGCDYBZHCRKAO7", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Sidereal Magic", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/trades/academics-astronomy-navigation-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You know the @Compendium[undertaking.spells-cantrips.0UML5AJIEZESNC56]{Stability} cantrip. When you reach 3rd level, you can cast the @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-1.7N5KBCOM40ZX65EO]{Arcane Arrows} spell once with this trait and regain the ability to do so when you finish a long rest. When you reach 5th level, you can cast the @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-2.XPI8O47UKUK45ZRP]{Weight of the World} spell once with this trait and regain the ability to do so when you finish a long rest. Intelligence, Wisdom, or Presence is your spellcasting attribute for it (chosen when you select this race).</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "SZB7LUSQ2DP1Z38K", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Sublime Descent", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/light/projectiles-star-purple.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Creatures of your choice within 10 feet of you have resistance to damage caused by falling.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "ATC9IW4AOMA74635", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Twilight Messenger", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/documents/document-letter-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You know the @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-level-1.OK48R80X6F22TZ7D]{Magic Missive} spell, and can cast it as a ritual. When you cast the spell, the missive folds into the shape of a moth while in flight.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "5VBCE0TI5ROEEH8N", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Weak Build", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/death/hand-withered-gray.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your carrying capacity is reduced to \u00e2\u2026\u201d the normal amount, and you cannot grapple, trip, or shove creatures larger than you.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "core"}, "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "5FAD194X1HDZFU2U", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Amphibious", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/amphibians/frog-water-teal.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You can breathe air and water.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "core"}, "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "FIAKA97FYXBI8RXA", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Crushing Bite", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/reptiles/lizard-mouth-glowing-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your powerful jaws function as a natural weapon that deals bludgeoning damage equal to 1d6 plus your Strength modifier on a hit. You are proficient with your jaws, but they do not grant any extra attacks, actions, or minor actions on their own.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "XTBTJVESG8QZXIDM", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Deep Ocean Adaptation", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/fish/fish-bioluminous-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You are adapted to the ocean's depths and do not suffer adverse effects of being in those environments.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "Z8LMDPJW67U417SF", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Elemental Equilibrium", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/trading-justice-scale-gold.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>After you cast a spell that deals cold or fire damage, you gain the condition <strong>Cold Attuned</strong> or <strong>Fire Attuned</strong> respectively, which are detailed below:</p><ul><li>Cold Attuned: When you cast a spell that deals cold damage, you and one target damaged by the spell before it ends suffer 1d4 cold damage. This condition ends after 1 minute or when you cast a spell that deals fire damage.</li><li><strong>Fire Attuned:</strong> When you cast a spell that deals fire damage, you and one target damaged by the spell before it ends suffer 1d4 fire damage. This condition ends after 1 minute or when you cast a spell that deals cold damage.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "614UPFMARNM1ROVC", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Extremophile", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/death/skeleton-fish-teal.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have resistance to fire and cold damage.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "ZSFV2WOU1HUP17KZ", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Fearless", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/control/fear-fright-white.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have advantage on saving throws made to resist being @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.UK95BQ45TGSD5Q3V]{Frightened}.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "NG4N84ST7ES1J9IE", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Heat Transfer", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/earth/lava-explosion-orange.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You know the @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.58I1UTE8ZV4CJ5W6]{Adherent Ember} and @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.KH6D03TEJYZNA62N]{Deposition} cantrips. Your spellcasting ability for them is Intelligence, Wisdom, or Presence, chosen when you select this race. The material components for Adherent Ember are replaced with volcanic rocks (consumed by the spell) which the spell heats to near molten.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "LSXJQMNO1E738IQC", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Inject Venom", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/wounds/blood-cells-disease-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When you hit a creature with your bite, you can choose to deal an additional 2d4 poison damage. Once you use this ability, you can't use it again until you finish a rest.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "PT5XC6EU86D58ODI", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Moist Skin", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/amphibians/frog-water-teal.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Whenever you spend an hour in an environment of extreme heat (such as a desert during daytime or terrain with exposed lava), you gain a level of @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.ERBR3AG01H4N1L91]{Exhaustion} if you don't already have any. In addition to the normal rules for resting, exhaustion imposed by this trait can be removed by fully submerging yourself in water.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "core"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "OQYT9KI73HD5VRJI", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Natural Regeneration", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/life/heart-shadow-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>If you lose an eye or appendage, it grows back over the course of 7 days. Whenever you spend a rest die to regain hit points, you can regain extra hit points on a low roll, as detailed below:</p><ul><li>D4 rest die: When you roll a 2 or lower on the die, add 2 to the total.</li><li>D6 rest die: When you roll a 3 or lower on the die, add 3 to the total.</li><li>D8 rest die: When you roll a 4 or lower on the die, add 4 to the total.</li><li>D10 rest die: When you roll a 5 or lower on the die, add 5 to the total.</li><li>D12 rest die: When you roll a 6 or lower on the die, add 6 to the total.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "NZF69C583MKEQ0PB", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Resist Toxins", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/toxins/cup-goblet-poisoned-spilled.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have resistance to poison damage and advantage on saves made to avoid being @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.9X088PM7H5U2S1HQ]{Sickened} or @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.SRRBLPRSJWGUR551]{Poisoned}.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "2PRN9S8X7YFBJP10", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Secrete Toxin", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/amphibians/bullfrog-glowing-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When a creature within 5 feet of you hits you with a melee attack, you can use your reaction to cause the attacker to take 1d4 points of poison damage. You can use this ability a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and regain all uses when you finish a rest.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "EZ51QFJQ8CC1P3GQ", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Bull Rush", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/mammals/ox-bull-horned-glowing-orange.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When you Dash, you gain an additional 10 feet of movement and can make one attack using your Horns as a non-action before the end of your turn.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "core"}, "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "LGWWYVXE4UCUIR9I", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Heavy Hitter", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When you attack with a melee weapon that lacks the Light property, a ranged weapon that has the Heavy property, or a natural weapon, the weapon's damage die is increased by one step.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "666YST9UQN7QPICB", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
